{"title":"GCSE (A* to G) qualification-level conditions and requirements","public_updated_at":"2017-02-16T15:14:48Z","details":{"body":"<div class=\"govspeak\"><p>These documents set out rules and regulations for all GCSEs (A* to G).</p>\n\n<p>Read the associated <a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/gcse-a-to-g-qualification-level-guidance\">guidance</a> to understand how to comply with these rules.</p>\n\n<p>You should also read our <a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/guidance/awarding-organisations-understanding-our-regulatory-requirements#requirements-for-all-awarding-organisations-and-all-regulated-qualifications\">requirements for all qualifications</a>, as well as our <a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/gcses-a-to-g-requirements-and-guidance\">other rules for GCSEs (A* to G)</a>.</p>\n\n<h3 id=\"february-2017\">February 2017</h3>\n\n<p>We have published our Requirements for key dates which come into force on 1 May 2017. These are requirements which an awarding organisation must comply with from that date, when it specifies deadlines for requesting reviews of marking, reviews of moderation and appeals. For more information see our <a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/news/further-decisions-on-reviews-of-marking-reviews-of-moderation-and-appeals\">announcement</a>.</p>\n</div>","change_history":[{"public_timestamp":"2017-02-16T15:14:48.000+00:00","note":"Published requirements for key dates for reviews of marking, reviews of moderation and appeals."},{"public_timestamp":"2016-08-25T08:15:21.000+01:00","note":"Updated following introduction of our rules and guidance for enquiries and appeals"},{"public_timestamp":"2016-07-15T17:04:27.000+01:00","note":"Added regulations for reviews and appeals."},{"public_timestamp":"2016-06-24T12:01:00.000+01:00","note":"First published."}],"documents":["<section class=\"attachment embedded\" id=\"attachment_1962567\">\n  <div class=\"attachment-thumb\">\n      <a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"thumbnai